text: Hurricane Otto was a strong tropical cyclone in November 2016. The storm was the southernmost hurricane on record to hit Central America. It was also the first Atlantic storm to survive the crossover into the Pacific Ocean since Hurricane Cesar-Douglas in 1996. Otto started late on November 21 in the southwest Caribbean Sea. Costa Rica, southern Nicaragua and Panama had heavy damage from the storm. At least 23 people died because of Hurricane Otto.
